  "texts": [
    "Second, the measured value can be subject to statistical and systematic biases.",
    "We have in fact shown that even when a power law with γ = 13/3 is injected into the data, the measured values can be biased due to the statistical realization of the noise.",
    "Moreover, the mis-modeling of highfrequency noise can systematically bias the recovered γ, leading to flatter spectra if unaccounted high-frequency noise is present in the data.",
    "Therefore, caution should be taken when drawing conclusions from this measurement.",
    "Conversely, a shallow spectral slope might indicate that the GW signal has a different origin, perhaps from some key physical process occurring in the early Universe, as investigated in Sect. 4."
